						               													<description>One Minute Bulge is an Operational level wargame depicting the Ardennes Campaign that began on December 16, 1944. This is a solitaire challenge with the player representing a group of high-ranking German military commanders like von Rundstedt, Model, Dietrich, and von Manteuffel. The player must strive to achieve a decisive victory by capturing Antwerp while avoid a confrontation with the volatile Fuhrer.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Playing time is approximately one minute. Counters depict the seven armies that participated in the campaign... Patton's 3rd Army, the 6th Panzer Army, etc. Map scale is about 75 miles to the hex. The single turn represents about two or three weeks of action. Rules include surprise attack, weather, supply depots, and the dreaded Fuhrer Conference.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This is intended to be a free &amp;quot;Print &amp;amp; Play&amp;quot; game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
